    "It's not merely about creating an AI that can mimic human behavior in certain contexts or for limited durations, but about developing an AI that can genuinely replicate the full spectrum of human cognitive abilities in a way that is indistinguishable from a human across all contexts and over an extended period.",
    "That was very good.",
    "Now, whereas I have emphasized total capacity in both the T2 and the T3 case, there is a reasonable question about the extent of generic sensorimotor capacity in the case of T3, as in the example we discussed of Helen Keller.",
    "She was distinguishable from a normal person in that she was blind and deaf, but she clearly had all the sensorimotor capacity that was needed to ground T2 verbal capacity.",
    "Do you agree?"
